{"title":"In the Drops: Truflo electric mini pump, Comfy Lizard Skins bar tape, the Pogačar biography, magic broccoli juice and Connie Converse & co","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/truflo-electron-electric-mini-pump","date":1771607456000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/truflo-electron-electric-mini-pump\">In the Drops: Truflo electric mini pump, Comfy Lizard Skins bar tape, the Pogačar biography, magic broccoli juice and Connie Converse &amp; co</a></p>\n\n<p>By the end of next week it will be March, which – by <em>some</em> measures, at least – is spring. We did it. Congrats everyone.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve been quite busy at Cyclist doing our best to enjoy the penultimate throes of this wet winter. We gave <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/\">our homepage</a> a shake-up (hopefully you like it), welcomed the new Cannondale SuperSix with an <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cannondale-supersix-evo-2026\">in-depth news story</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/cannondale-supersix-evo-2026-review\">first ride review</a>, and enjoyed the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/uae-tour-men-preview\">UAE Tour </a>and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/volta-ao-algarve-preview\">Volta ao Algarve</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We also assessed <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/what-is-happening-at-visma-lease-a-bike\">the goings on at Visma-Lease a Bike</a>, had a look at <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/underdogs-classics-2026\">who might have the faintest chance to win a big Classic</a> and is not named Tadej or Mathieu, questioned <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/remco-evenepoel-unreliable\">Remco Evenepoel’s GC potential </a>and asked <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/decathlon-cma-cgm-superteam\">if Paul Seixas’s Decathlon-CMA CGM are the next great superteam</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And finally, the latest episode of the podcast is a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pieter-potters-eddy-merckx-podcast\">lovely interview with bike designer Pieter Potters</a>, who works on Ridley and Eddy Merckx bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get to it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=NewsletterBanner1\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-970x332.webp\" alt=\"'sign up to the cyclist newsletter' banner, saying 'opinions, offers, insights and updates'\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-970x332.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-300x103.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-768x263.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-1536x526.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-2048x701.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-750x257.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/05/Newsletter-flash-v2-1-1140x390.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Truflo Electron mini pump</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-scaled.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-scaled.webp 2560w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-truflo-1-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Electric mini pumps are taking over, and Truflo has recently joined the party with this, the Electron. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s compact, has a big digital screen, pumps to 120psi with a claimed +/-1psi accuracy and is said to be able to seat tubeless tyres. Truflo says on a test with 700x38c tyres one full charge provided approximately three inflations to 50psi from flat.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It comes with a hose included for cleaner inflation as well as a needle for pumping balls if you’re that way inclined. Truflo says it weighs 118g.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy it now from <a href=\"https://www.freewheel.co.uk/truflo-electron-compact-electric-pump-qa5000\" target=\"_blank\">Freewheel (£49.99)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Lizard Skins DSP Ultra bar tape</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-lizard-skins-1-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As my erstwhile colleague Matthew Loveridge noted in <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/van-rysel-rcr-f-pro-road-bike-review\">his review of the Van Rysel RCR-F,</a> handlebars and bar tape are the most undervalued parts of any bike build. Never underestimate the power of good bar tape, like Lizard Skins’ new DSP Ultra. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s for both road and gravel – an easy indicator that it should be comfy – and features the ‘next generation’ DuraSoft polymer construction, which is claimed to help with both vibration damping and durability – hence the ‘Ultra’ label.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It also has an extra-grippy texture and reliable adhesive to prevent slipping no matter how wet or sweaty it might be. It comes in thicknesses of 1.9mm, 2.7mm or 3.5mm and loads of colour options, but this one is clearly the best.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy it now from <a href=\"https://www.silverfish-uk.com/lizard-skins-dsp-ultra-bar-tape.html\" target=\"_blank\">Silverfish (from £49.99)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            \r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pieter-potters-eddy-merckx-podcast\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/belgian-cycling-factory-150x150.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/belgian-cycling-factory-150x150.webp 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/belgian-cycling-factory-45x45.webp 45w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/belgian-cycling-factory-75x75.webp 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/belgian-cycling-factory-350x350.webp 350w\" alt=\"belgian-cycling-factory-150x150.webp\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>Cyclist Magazine Podcast: UCI rules, design evolution, and why bikes are so expensive, with Pieter Potters</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/cannondale-supersix-evo-2026-review\">\r\n                                            <div>