<div>\r\n                                                <h4>The new Cannondale SuperSix Evo kills off the SystemSix</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article>\r\n                                    <article>\r\n                                        <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paul-seixas-interview\">\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/12/file-38-150x150.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/12/file-38-150x150.webp 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/12/file-38-75x75.webp 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/12/file-38-350x350.webp 350w\" alt=\"file-38-150x150.webp\" />\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <h4>'The harder it is, the better': Interview with Paul Seixas, the next great French hope</h4>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </a>\r\n                                    </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2><em>Tadej Pogačar: Unstoppable</em> by Andy McGrath</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-pog-book-1-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Tadej Pogačar is seemingly unstoppable, hence why occasional Cyclist writer Andy McGrath’s new book is called just that. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s claimed to be the first biography of the greatest cyclist of all time, tracking his life from his upbringing in Slovenia and getting the inside scoop from those closest to him as well as his rivals.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy it now from <a href=\"https://www.bloomsbury.com/uk/tadej-pogacar-9781399426541/\" target=\"_blank\">Bloomsbury (£14)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Nomio shots</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/itd-nomio-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Buckle up, because the latest performance secret to be unlocked by science is… broccoli. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, the Swedish boffins at Nomio have produced a drink made with mostly broccoli sprout extracts (the other 20% is lemon and sugar) that’s claimed to help reduce lactate, handle high training loads and quicken recovery thanks to chemicals called ITC (isothiocyanates).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nomio says ITC is known to activate the body’s stress regulator, which essentially helps the body to handle hard exercise. Be sure to visit Nomio’s website below for the actual, more scientific description of how it’s meant to work. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To bring it back to cycling specifically, Mads Pedersen is big into it.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>For more information and to buy it now from <a href=\"https://drinknomio.com/en-gb/products/nomio-i-6\" target=\"_blank\">Nomio (£20 box)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>What we’re into this week: Post-radio music discovery</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Say what you like about TikTok and co, but you can’t deny that it’s been a good thing for music. Yes there are annoying TikTok songs, but on the whole, it’s bringing a massive range of actually good music to younger audiences. Fleetwood Mac got back in the charts, Djo took over the world, and Labi Siffre got so viral he’s releasing a new album at 80 years old. Gone are the days when the only music people heard was whatever was playing on Capital FM or Radio 1. Thank the lord.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I’ll also give some reluctant credit to the algorithm in saying that Spotify’s ‘made for you’ playlists have put me on to some new favourites. My go-to at the moment is the ‘Cottagecore Mix’, which currently includes Labi Siffre as well as Connie Converse. If you don’t know, Converse was a folk singer-songwriter active in the 1950s who didn’t break through at the time but after old recordings were published she’s gained plenty of fans 70 years too late. She was certainly ahead of her time, I highly recommend having a listen and then looking up her crazy story.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I previously included playlists of new music I like in this section but have gone off the boil, so I’m going to start a new one that I’ll keep going with my current rotation of songs I’m enjoying rather than exclusively new discoveries. You can find that <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/playlist/3LOiH6gRw8ma49kEJcaUdH?si=hEzY0Mw3Sj6OysujX-iHTg\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>, it’s not got loads in at the moment but I’ll keep adding and removing.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature</strong></em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Boyd Cycling’s gravel wheel range covers high-speed racers and real-world riders</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2528\" height=\"1696\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking.webp 2528w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking-300x201.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking-970x651.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking-768x515.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking-1536x1030.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking-2048x1374.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking-750x503.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Reiver-bikepacking-1140x765.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>At Boyd Cycling, performance has never been one-size-fits-all. At the very top of its gravel lineup sits the Jocassee SL, the no-compromise gravel wheelset built with aerospace-grade carbon fiber and the brand’s flagship Grade 54 hubs. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With lightning-fast engagement and an obsessively refined carbon layup, the Jocassee SL tips the scales at an incredible 1,145g. However, the strength of the rim rivals that of a mountain bike wheelset. That’s a goal most brands struggle to approach, let alone beat, even at weights north of 1,400g. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Jocassee SL exists to prove what’s possible when wheel design, materials selection, and build spec have no limit. But that isn’t the only story Boyd Cycling wants to tell. Boyd believes great gravel wheels shouldn’t be reserved for just those riders chasing the cutting edge of wheel design. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why it built the Reiver.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Reiver brings true carbon gravel performance to a more accessible price point without losing the durability and ride quality that matter when gravel turns rough. With a 26mm internal-width carbon rim, Grade 36 hubs with 10° of engagement, and a proven spoke and brass nipple build, the Reiver is designed for punishing terrain – not pristine racecourses. At just 1,385g per set and priced at only $1,200, the Reiver delivers serious performance where it counts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>From the uncompromising Jocassee SL to the value-driven Reiver, Boyd Cycling remains committed to building wheels for how people actually ride gravel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Two paths. One philosophy. Built to ride hard!</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<div><a href=\"https://www.boydcycling.com/shop/category/gravel-wheels-carbon-gravel-wheels-87\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Find out more</strong></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature ends</strong></em></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+3\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"970\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-970x250.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-970x250.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-300x77.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-768x198.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-1536x396.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-2048x528.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-750x193.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2026/02/Subs-flash-172-for-web-3-new-1140x294.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/truflo-electron-electric-mini-pump\">In the Drops: Truflo electric mini pump, Comfy Lizard Skins bar tape, the Pogačar biography, magic broccoli juice and Connie Converse &amp; co</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Will Strickson &#124; Website Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"9d0c3f6cc08f295106c106bdfdaf14f9e131979d17bbf031a6aef1b3a8eb2b59","category":"Cycling"}